comments.content:
@Sii: about topography: I don’t think you can modify the font used on the map that easily. I’m curious as to why they used Myriad (or, the reason why the default map typeface was set to that.)

Also, I think you meant to say that Dewmocracy “jumped on the Obama 2008 bandwagon,” yes? Because the site’s font is Gill :-)

I had actually [attempted to type-ID](http://web.archive.org/web/20150218043341/http:/linkenfuego.wordpress.com/2008/01/04/q-have-anyone-on-the-internet-identified-the-fonts-that-the-2008-presidential-candidates-used-in-their-campaign-logos-side-by-side/) all of the 2008 presidential campaign logo a day before this topic was started—with moderate level of success. I believe that I was right in most of them, but I’m nowhere as typographically geeky as all you guys, so kindly drop a line if I was wrong.
